<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>PUBLIC ADMINISTRATION SELECT COMMITTEE</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:26pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence from the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:26pt; font-weight:bold">Public Administration Select Committee (PASC)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:26pt; font-weight:bold"> (SCE0017)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:26pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt">This note responds to the Liaison Committee’s </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt">short inquiry to follow up the recommendations made in its 2012 report into Select committee effectiveness, resources and powers.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold">Innovation and good practice</span></p><p style="font-size:18pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:18pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.28pt; padding-left:4.72pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; text-decoration:underline">Inquiries</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt">: in June 2012, the Committee agreed a programme of work on “statistics and their use in government”, which they planned to handle by way of ten mini inquiries into various aspects of this broad topic. Some of the topics have been investigated through a short, traditional select committee inquiry; others have been handled through correspondence. The Committee is about two thirds through the programme of work, and at the end of the programme, the success of this way of working will be evaluated.</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:18pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:18pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.28pt; padding-left:4.72pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt">The Committee has also been experimenting with the use of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt">rapporteurs</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt">, in particular, in their work on financial scrutiny; the effectiveness of this approach will also be evaluated. </span></li></ul><p style="font-size:18pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:18pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 13.28pt; padding-left:4.72pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; text-decoration:underline">Outreach</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt">: the Committee recently initiated a thread on the website Money Saving Expert, to see views to inform its inquiry into complaints handling. This was done with the help of the Outreach Team. It generated some interesting comments. </span></li></ul><p style="font-size:18pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:18pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt">The Committee will shortly hear from members of the public with experience of complaining about public services, in an informal seminar, in order to inform its inquiry into complaints handling.</span></p><p style="font-size:18pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:18pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 12pt 13.28pt; padding-left:4.72pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; text-decoration:underline">Electronic working</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt">: both Committee Members and staff find electronic circulation of papers an effective way of working. In particular, the circulation template, created by the Science and Technology clerk, is a good way of presenting the circulation in a user-friendly way.</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:18pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><br style="page-break-before:always; clear:both" /></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold">PASC work against core tasks (June 2012 to October 2013)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:16.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:16.5pt">SELECT COMMITTEE CORE TASKS FOR DEPARTMENTAL SELECT COMMITTEES </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:16.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:16.5pt">Overall aim: To hold Ministers and Departments to account for their policy and decision-making and to support the House in its control of the supply of public money and scrutiny of legislation </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:16.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:16.5pt">STRATEGY </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:16.5pt">Task 1: To examine the strategy of the department, how it has identified its key objectives and priorities and whether it has the means to achieve them, in terms of plans, resources, skills, capabilities and management information </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:16.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:16.5pt">POLICY </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:16.5pt">Task 2: To examine policy proposals by the department, and areas of emerging policy, or where existing policy is deficient, and make proposals </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:16.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:16.5pt">EXPENDITURE AND PERFORMANCE </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:16.5pt">Task 3: To examine the expenditure plans, outturn and performance of the department and its arm’s length bodies, and the relationships between spending and delivery of outcomes </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:16.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:16.5pt">DRAFT BILLS </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:16.5pt">Task 4: To conduct scrutiny of draft bills within the committee’s responsibilities </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:16.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:16.5pt">BILLS AND DELEGATED LEGISLATION </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:16.5pt">Task 5: To assist the House in its consideration of bills and statutory instruments, including draft orders under the Public Bodies Act </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:16.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:16.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:16.5pt">POST-LEGISLATIVE SCRUTINY </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:16.5pt">Task 6: To examine the implementation of legislation and scrutinise the department’s post- legislative assessments </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:16.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:16.5pt">EUROPEAN SCRUTINY </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:16.5pt">Task 7: To scrutinise policy developments at the European level and EU legislative proposals </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:16.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:16.5pt">APPOINTMENTS </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:16.5pt">Task 8: To scrutinise major appointments made by the department and to hold pre-appointment hearings where appropriate </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:16.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:16.5pt">SUPPORT FOR THE HOUSE </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:16.5pt">Task 9: To produce timely reports to inform debate in the House, including Westminster Hall, or debating committees, and to examine petitions tabled </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:16.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:16.5pt">PUBLIC ENGAGEMENT </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:16.5pt">Task 10: To assist the House of Commons in better engaging with the public by ensuring that the work of the committee is accessible to the public </span></p><p style="font-size:18pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 20pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:18pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 20pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:18pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 20pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:18pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 20pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Std 45 Light'; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" style="border-collapse:collapse; margin-left:0pt"><tr><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-t