commend that the usual template for committee reports be changed to distinguish clearly the recommendations targeted at the Government. We suggest that conclusions should be in bold, with recommendations in bold italics, and that it should be clearly stated to whom the recommendation is addressed.</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:30.38%"><p style="font-size:18pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 20pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt">PASC reports do format conclusions in bold and recommendations in bold italics with the target of the recommendation clearly stated.</span></p><p style="font-size:18pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 20pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt">PASC reports do not stipulate which recommendations are the most important to PASC.</span></p></td><td style="border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-left-style:solid; border-left-width:0.5pt; border-right-color:#000000; border-right-style:solid; border-right-width:0.5pt; border-top-color:#000000; border-top-style:solid; border-top-width:0.5pt; padding-left:5.4pt; padding-right:5.4pt; vertical-align:top; width:19.72%"><p style="font-size:18pt; line-height:150%; margin:0pt 0pt 20pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt">Committee to discuss the advantages and disadvantages of identifying in Committee reports which recommendations are the most important.</span></p></td><td style="background-color:#f79646; border-bottom-color:#000000; border-bottom-style:solid; border-bottom-width:0.5pt; border-left-color:#000000; border-